node.text: On this Surly Speaks, we take a look at Surly bike's versatility and customization. You see, at Surly we believe a bike should be purpose-built for the type of riding that you want to do. And we also think it’s pretty great when a person’s bike is a reflection of their personal style. So, because of this, we design and engineer our bikes with versatility and customization in mind, so that you can make it your own. Ultimately, we humanoids are all unique individuals. So why should we ride identical bikes?

node.title: Surly Speaks | Make It Your Own

Introducing the Surly Corner Bar!⁠
⁠
Grab a roll of quarters for the jukebox and saunter over to the Corner Bar, a mind-bending specimen that lets you ride in a drop-bar hand position while running your current mountain drivetrain and brake levers, saving you from buying all sorts of expensive drop-bar parts. ⁠
⁠
Forged from Chromoly Steel and coming in three widths (46, 50, 54), it’ll land at North American Surly dealers in early September. International Humanoids, please inquire at your local bike shop for availability. For all the steely details and a complete list of retailers, head on over to the link in our bio. ⁠
⁠
#surlycornerbar #surlybikes #dirtdrops #weirdbarsstartlives⁠
